"(b) Confidentiality of Information.

(A) The scope of the representation;

(B) The basis or rate of the representation;

(C) The extent of the lawyer's authority to represent the client;

(D) The time by which the lawyer must take action; and

(E) The fee to be charged.

Therefore, lawyers from different law firms providing legal services to a client on a particular matter must consult with each other and the client about the scope of their respective representations, as well as other important issues related to the representation.
